      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Harvey Araton's column ("Short-Term Formula Key for Blue Jays," The Times, Aug. 3) on the Blue Jays is one part drivel, two parts envy and three parts sour grapes.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Harvey Araton's column ("Short-Term Formula Key for Blue Jays," The Times, Aug. 3) on the Blue Jays is one part drivel, two parts envy and three parts sour grapes.</p>
        <p>As to his remark about Skydome falling down, he should visit Maple Leaf Gardens built in 1931 (thus outlasting successive Madison Square Gardens). And perhaps he should consider Peter Ustinov's line: "Toronto is New York as it would be run by the Swiss."  HENRY H. WEBSTER  Roseville, Minn.</p>
      </block>
